== Lower cost meal plan ==

10 eggs + 150g good cheese = 4.5e
    (14e/kg cheese)
    450 + 700 = 1150 cal
5 steaks haché + 5 cheddar : 5.9
    or
5 steaks haché + 100g good cheese : 6.5
    1250 calories

You can have :
0.5kg chicken per week
0.5kg mackerel per week
300g mozza per week

total = 330e/month
---
6 eggs + 100g good cheese = 2.9
    300 + 420 = 720 cal

7 (steak haché + 20g cheese) = 9.1
    1820 cal

You can have :
0.5kg chicken per week
0.5kg mackerel per week
300g mozza per week

total = 360e/month
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


600g chicken every 2 weeks
    fried dumsticks, thighs
    fried wings (use only protein powder)
    fried nuggets
    fried tenders
        thighs : chicken fingers, seared with skin
            https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TDUcQhOzO1Q
    cuisses poulet roti

500g fish every 2 weeks
    oven baked : sardines, maqueraux
    fried fish : cabillaud, merlu, sole, merlan, others

300-500g frozen seafood
    fruits de mer : crevettes, gambas, noix saint-jaques, encornet, poulpe, moules, crabe
        plancha + some sauce
    fried fish : cabillaud



6 eggs/day
    soft boiled
    medium boiled
    fried whole
    scrambled
        + butter
        + cheese
        + creme fraiche
        + some meat : merguez, crevette, jambon...

1.5kg agneau : gigot tranches, cotes
    sometimes : poitrine
3 tranches 300g entrecote/faux filet

1kg steak haché to fill the blanks
    + cheddar on top

100-150g cheese/day
    AOP/IGP lait cru : to eat raw
    AOP/IGP pasteurisé : sauce, with eggs
    other cheeses : fried
    cheddar + fake cheddar : for steaks

lamb liver : 200g every 2 weeks
    or buy one liver and freeze

Sometimes:
    fressure/abats : rognons, poumon, coeur
    tete agneau
    merguez

